    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="1254"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1254">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/396.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Bevan</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 15, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following advice this office American firms have not paid tax and so far no
                    forceful measures have been adopted by Nafarrate, Several <pb facs="0872"
                        n="756" xml:id="pg_756"/> Spanish firms have paid. Clerks of other Spanish
                    firms who refused to pay are now in jail for not making payments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bevan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
